    "metaTitle": "About — Daniel Epler Nuñez",
    "hero": {
      "heading": "About me",
      "lede": "Product designer working at the intersection of people, technology, and practice — driven by the moments when a product just works.",
      "facts": [
        "Odense, Denmark",
        "MSc IT Product Design",
        "Danish · English · Spanish"
      ]
    },
    "portrait": {
      "src": "portrait.png",
      "alt": "Portrait of Daniel Epler Nuñez"
    },
    "paragraphs": [
      "I'm a product designer with an MSc in IT Product Design from the University of Southern Denmark (grade average 12). I work where people, technology, and everyday practice meet: understanding users and their workflows, finding the friction, and turning insights into prototypes and decisions people can act on.",
      "That has taken me from UX consulting at FIVE — where I redesigned a health app's onboarding from 18 steps to 3 — to AI research and teaching at SDU, investigating how generative AI reshapes competency needs and showing students how to treat AI as a design material. From the first field interview to the 3D-printed model in someone's hand, I like making ideas concrete enough to test.",
      "What drives me are products with exceptional user experiences — the ones that offer seamless, effortless joy in their use. I'm calm and curious, structured when problems are unclear, and happiest in interdisciplinary teams gathering different perspectives around a shared direction."
    ],
